modules.description: This module defines a type `t` for representing formatted output, specifically supporting `Markdown` with a title and content string, or plain `Text`. It provides operations to construct, match, and render these formatted values. Use cases include generating structured output for documentation or UI displays where content needs explicit formatting.

This module defines a context type used to configure LSIF-related operations, including the LSIF endpoint, repository identifier, and formatting settings. It works with strings and a formatting type to store configuration data needed for interacting with LSIF services. Concrete use cases include setting up request contexts for querying LSIF data or formatting responses from an LSIF server.

This module provides a `hover_at` function that queries LSIF data for hover information at a specific file position, using a context configured with repository and formatting settings. It works with string paths, integer line/column positions, and structured formatting types to retrieve and present code intelligence. Concrete use cases include integrating with editors or IDEs to display type information, documentation, or definitions inline during code navigation.

The module includes a `hover_at` function that retrieves LSIF hover information for a given file path and position, using repository and formatting settings. It operates on string paths, integer line and column numbers, and formatting types to deliver code intelligence. This supports use cases like displaying inline documentation, type details, or definitions in editors during code navigation.
